â”‚  WIRING PREPARATION:                                   â”‚
â”‚                                                        â”‚
â”‚  1. Cut speaker wire (2-core, red+black)               â”‚
â”‚     Length: 15-25cm per speaker                        â”‚
â”‚                                                        â”‚
â”‚  2. Strip both ends (5mm)                              â”‚
â”‚                                                        â”‚
â”‚  3. Twist strands tightly                              â”‚
â”‚                                                        â”‚
â”‚  4. Tin the ends with solder                           â”‚
â”‚                                                        â”‚
â”‚  FOR SOLDER TABS (TYPE A):                             â”‚
â”‚  â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€                             â”‚
â”‚                                                        â”‚
â”‚  a) Clean tab with isopropyl alcohol                   â”‚
â”‚                                                        â”‚
â”‚  b) Apply tiny bit of flux to tab                      â”‚
â”‚                                                        â”‚
â”‚  c) Tin the tab:                                       â”‚
â”‚     â”Œâ”€â”€â”                â”Œâ”€â”€â”                           â”‚
