PHOTO 21: Audio System Testing
â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•
â”Œâ”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”
â”‚  STEP 5.5: Test audio before mounting in box           â”‚
â”‚                                                        â”‚
â”‚  SAFETY FIRST:                                         â”‚
â”‚  â€¢ Start with volume potentiometer at MINIMUM          â”‚
â”‚  â€¢ Gradually increase volume                           â”‚
â”‚  â€¢ Avoid feedback (speaker near mic)                   â”‚
â”‚                                                        â”‚
â”‚  TEST PROCEDURE:                                       â”‚
â”‚                                                        â”‚
â”‚  1. Power on RPi with all connections made             â”‚
â”‚                                                        â”‚
â”‚  2. In terminal, run:                                  â”‚
â”‚     bash                                            â”‚ â”‚     speaker-test -t wav -c 2                           â”‚ â”‚                                                     â”‚
â”‚                                                        â”‚
â”‚  3. You should hear:                                   â”‚
â”‚     "Front Left" â†’ Left speaker                        â”‚
â”‚     "Front Right" â†’ Right speaker                      â”‚
â”‚                                                        â”‚
â”‚  4. If no sound:                                       â”‚
â”‚     a) Check volume on PAM8403 pot (turn clockwise)    â”‚
â”‚     b) Check RPi volume: alsamixer                     â”‚
â”‚     c) Verify 3.5mm jack is fully inserted             â”‚
â”‚     d) Check all screw terminals are tight             â”‚
â”‚                                                        â”‚
â”‚  5. If sound only from one speaker:                    â”‚
â”‚     a) Swap L and R wires (test which speaker broken)  â”‚
â”‚     b) Check solder joints on bad speaker              â”‚
â”‚     c) Test speaker with multimeter (should be 4-8Î©)   â”‚
â”‚                                                        â”‚
â”‚  6. If sound is distorted:                             â”‚
â”‚     a) Lower volume (may be clipping)                  â”‚
â”‚     b) Check power supply (need stable 5V)             â”‚
â”‚     c) Verify speaker impedance matches (4Î©)           â”‚
â”‚                                                        â”‚
â”‚  QUALITY CHECK:                                        â”‚
â”‚  â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€                                      â”‚
â”‚  âœ“ Clear sound, no crackling                           â”‚
â”‚  âœ“ Both speakers equal volume                          â”‚
â”‚  âœ“ No buzzing or humming                               â”‚
â”‚  âœ“ Volume control works smoothly                       â”‚
â”‚  âœ“ Bass and treble sound natural                       â”‚
â”‚                                                        â”‚
â”‚  VOLUME CALIBRATION:                                   â”‚
â”‚  â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€                                  â”‚
â”‚  â€¢ Hardware pot (PAM8403): Set to 70-80%               â”‚
â”‚  â€¢ Software volume (alsamixer): Set to 80-90%          â”‚
â”‚  â€¢ In-game volume (PyGame): Set to 60-70%              â”‚
â”‚                                                        â”‚
â”‚  This gives best signal-to-noise ratio!                â”‚
â”‚                                                        â”‚
