ğŸ’¡ PRO TIPS
Button Placement:
ERGONOMICS:
- Most used buttons (A, B) = closest to thumb
- Less used (X, Y) = farther away
- START/SELECT = center (both hands reach)
- Shoulder buttons = top corners

SPACING:
- Between buttons: 3-5mm gap
- Joystick to buttons: 8-10cm
- Height from table: comfortable wrist angle

TESTING:
- Mock up with cardboard FIRST!
- Test reach with your hands
- Verify no accidental presses
Color Psychology:
RED = Action, primary (Attack, Confirm)
BLUE = Secondary, special ability
GREEN = Positive, confirm, jump
YELLOW = Caution, item use
WHITE = System, neutral (Start, Select)
BLACK = Shoulder, advanced controls

