SIMPLE, STABLE, PERFECT! âœ…
â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•
PotrebujeÅ¡ pomoc s prvÃ½m bootom alebo PyGame setup? NapÃ­Å¡! ğŸš€ked dame buttons a joysticky do Adafruit Feather RP2040 bude to brat ako controllerDec 9ğŸ® ÃNO! Adafruit Feather RP2040 = USB HID Gamepad

âœ… KRÃTKA ODPOVEÄ:
ÃNO, Feather RP2040 dokÃ¡Å¾e emulovaÅ¥ USB gamepad!
RPi 5 ho uvidÃ­ ako "USB Controller" - funguje v PyGame automaticky.

ğŸ“Š FEATHER RP2040 vs KB2040:
FEATHER RP2040:
âœ… 4x ADC piny (A0, A1, A2, A3) â† PERFEKTNÃ‰!
âœ… USB-C
âœ… Built-in LiPo charger (BONUS!)
âœ… MenÅ¡Ã­ neÅ¾ KB2040
âœ… USB HID support

KB2040:
âœ… 4x ADC piny
âœ… USB-C  
âœ… STEMMA QT konektor
âŒ Å½iadny LiPo charger

BOTH: FungujÃº rovnako pre gamepad! âœ“

ğŸ”Œ ZAPOJENIE:
FEATHER RP2040:

A0 (ADC) â†’ Joystick L VRx
A1 (ADC) â†’ Joystick L VRy
A2 (ADC) â†’ Joystick R VRx
A3 (ADC) â†’ Joystick R VRy

GP5-GP14 â†’ 10x Buttons (digital)
GP15     â†’ Joystick L button (SW)
GP16     â†’ Joystick R button (SW)

GND      â†’ All grounds
3V3      â†’ Joystick VCC (both)

USB-C    â†’ RPi 5 USB port

ğŸ’» SOFTWARE (CircuitPython):
1. Install CircuitPython:
1. Download: https://circuitpython.org/board/adafruit_feather_rp2040/
2. Hold BOOTSEL button, plug USB
3. Drag .uf2 file to RPI-RP2 drive
4. Feather resets â†’ becomes CIRCUITPY drive
2. Install Libraries:
Download Adafruit CircuitPython Library Bundle:
https://circuitpython.org/libraries

Extract a skopÃ­ruj do CIRCUITPY/lib/:
- adafruit_hid/
- adafruit_gamepad.mpy (alebo analogio)
3. Code (code.py):
pythonimport board
import digitalio
import analogio
import usb_hid
from adafruit_hid.gamepad import Gamepad
import time

# Initialize USB HID Gamepad
gp = Gamepad(usb_hid.devices)

# Analog Joysticks
joy_l_x = analogio.AnalogIn(board.A0)
joy_l_y = analogio.AnalogIn(board.A1)
joy_r_x = analogio.AnalogIn(board.A2)
joy_r_y = analogio.AnalogIn(board.A3)

# Digital Buttons (10x)
buttons = []
button_pins = [board.GP5, board.GP6, board.GP7, board.GP8, board.GP9,
               board.GP10, board.GP11, board.GP12, board.GP13, board.GP14]

for pin in button_pins:
    button = digitalio.DigitalInOut(pin)
    button.direction = digitalio.Direction.INPUT
    button.pull = digitalio.Pull.UP  # Internal pull-up!
    buttons.append(button)

# Joystick buttons
joy_l_btn = digitalio.DigitalInOut(board.GP15)
joy_l_btn.direction = digitalio.Direction.INPUT
joy_l_btn.pull = digitalio.Pull.UP

joy_r_btn = digitalio.DigitalInOut(board.GP16)
joy_r_btn.direction = digitalio.Direction.INPUT
joy_r_btn.pull = digitalio.Pull.UP

def map_analog(value):
    """Map 0-65535 to -127 to 127"""
    return int((value / 65535) * 254 - 127)

# Main loop
while True:
    # Read analog joysticks
    lx = map_analog(joy_l_x.value)
    ly = map_analog(joy_l_y.value)
    rx = map_analog(joy_r_x.value)
    ry = map_analog(joy_r_y.value)
    
    # Read buttons (inverted because pull-up)
    button_states = 0
    for i, button in enumerate(buttons):
        if not button.value:  # Pressed = False (pull-up)
            button_states |= (1 << i)
    
    # Joystick buttons
    if not joy_l_btn.value:
        button_states |= (1 << 10)  # Button 11
    if not joy_r_btn.value:
        button_states |= (1 << 11)  # Button 12
    
    # Send HID report
    gp.move_joysticks(
        x=lx,
        y=ly,
        z=rx,
        r_z=ry
    )
    
    # Press/release buttons
    for i in range(12):
        if button_states & (1 << i):
            gp.press_buttons(i+1)
        else:
            gp.release_buttons(i+1)
    
    time.sleep(0.01)  # 100Hz polling

ğŸ–¥ï¸ NA RPi 5:
Test Äi funguje:
bash# Pripoj Feather cez USB k RPi 5

# Check devices
lsusb
# Should see: "Adafruit Feather RP2040"

# Test gamepad
jstest /dev/input/js0

# You should see:
# Axes: 4 (2 joysticks)
# Buttons: 12
V PyGame (automatic!):
pythonimport pygame

pygame.init()
pygame.joystick.init()

# Feather appears as joystick
joystick = pygame.joystick.Joystick(0)
joystick.init()

print(f"Joystick name: {joystick.get_name()}")
print(f"Axes: {joystick.get_numaxes()}")
print(f"Buttons: {joystick.get_numbuttons()}")

# Read in game loop:
while True:
    for event in pygame.event.get():
        if event.type == pygame.JOYBUTTONDOWN:
            print(f"Button {event.button} pressed")
        
        if event.type == pygame.JOYAXISMOTION:
            print(f"Axis {event.axis}: {event.value}")
```

**FUNGUJE AUTOMATICKY!** âœ…

